physical_examinations.relevant_findings: General: No acute distress; alert and fully oriented. Cardiac: Regular rate and rhythm; normal S1 and S2; no appreciable murmurs. Pulmonary: Lungs clear to auscultation bilaterally. Abdomen: Soft, non-distended, mild tenderness to palpation in the left lower quadrant and periumbilical regions; no rebound or guarding; (-) Rovsings and (-) Psoas signs; no scars. Extremities: Warm and well perfused.
